history.text: Hello. Have you seen John Wick?
I have not.  What is it about?
Keanu Reeves plays an ex-hitman that comes out of retirement.
There is tons of action and it is very unique in the way that it is shot and edited. It's kind of hard to explain.
Sounds interesting.  I haven't seen a lot of films with Keanu.  Do you know why he comes out of retirement?
He has a score to settle with a Russian crime syndicate.
They killed his puppy.
His puppy?!  That's awful!  Darn Russians!
Is it a violent film?
Very but its mostly hand-to-hand karate style fights but there are a lot of people that get shot. I don't remember if it was over the top but I don't think so.
Do you typically like movies like that?
Probably not.  I love action films, but I'm not big on violence or puppies being killed.  Plus, the last Keanu film I enjoyed was Speed, and that was over 20 years ago!
Though I did enjoy the film Keanu, but that was a comedy about a kitten named after the actor.  ;)
Ha, they don't show the puppy in this and I have seen that and its great.
Who else stars in John Wick?  Any female characters in it?
Yes, Adrianne Palicki plays a female contract killer, and Alfie Allen (GoT) plays a bad guy
Reeves is pretty funny in it, it definitely has humor element thrown in and it is well done. They trash a lot of SUVs
They also steal his car, I'm pretty sure it was a 70 Chevelle so he is a bit bitter.
I can't picture Alfie Allen as a villain, but I do like Adrianne Palicki.  She was great in Agents of Shield, and she's in Orville right now.  She can hold her own against Keanu.
Men and their cars. Hee hee.
How long ago was the movie released?
Yes, and of course he has to kill his way through 5 floors of baddies to get to the end boss. It was released in 2014.
Five floors of fighting?!  Does he have anyone on his side?
He does have some support, but he is pretty much a one man wrecking crew. I  would say border lining on superhero level
One man wrecking crew...interesting.
Didn't this movie have a sequel released recently?
I don't know about that. I do know that the first one set itself up for a franchise I think so I wouldn't be surprised.
Everything seems to be a franchise lately, or a reboot, but if the story and universe is good, I won't complain about a sequel.
I know that I enjoyed it and would watch a sequel for sure.
I do like watching hand-to-hand style combat if it is done well.
Keanu has lots of experience with that from the Matrix films, that's for sure!
Yes, and this film reminds me of the Matrix but in a different universe and John Wick is definitely not Nemo
Do you happen to remember the rating?  I wonder if it's too violent to have my teenage nephews watch it with me.
I don't know for sure, but I would guess R.
Alright, nice talking with you.

uid2response.feedback:
The user was fantastic for only going off the info given to them.  I'm not a big Keanu fan, so I'm passing on this one.  Plus, it sounds like they don't have many female characters. 
 Boo!  And they killed his puppy.  :(
